Lab51Py3 -- Inline shell for Python 3 developers.
 -provides IPython shell.
 -retrieves and installs <PyPI.org> packages.
 -builds EXEcutable (binary) applet.
 -establishes extension (.so) and source-code (.c) for making modules.
 -provides <sample.pyx> which might become handy with vectorization concept.
 
 Description: Lab51Py2 -- An inline shell for Python 2 developers.
 Lab51Py2 is an inline shell for productive development in Python 2:
 -provides an interactive IPython shell.
 -downloads and installs a package from the PyPI.org repo.
 -builds an EXEcutable (binary) file.
 -makes an extension (.so) and its source-code in (.c).
 -provides a <sample.pyx> that helps with vectorization concept.
 
 	echo 'pattern: lab51py2 [OPTION]... [FILE]...'
	echo ' '
	echo '--------------------------------------------------------'
	echo 'The Lab51Py2 is an inline shell for Python 2 developers.'
	echo 'contact: https://github.com/vspades'
	echo '--------------------------------------------------------'
	echo ' '
	echo -e '--help\t\t\t\tdisplays this help.'
	echo ' '
	echo -e '--ipython\t\t\tprovides an interactive IPython shell.'
	echo ' '
	echo -e '--pkg <PyPI-package>\t\tdownloads and installs a package from the'
	echo -e '\t\t\t\tPyPI.org repo.'
	echo ' '
	echo -e '--build <python-script(.py)>\tbuilds an EXEcutable (binary) file.'
	echo ' '
	echo -e '--mod <cython-script(.pyx)>\tmakes an extension (.so).'
	echo -e '\t\t\t\t/home/'$USER'/.area51py2/lib/sample.pyx'

Description: Py2Lab51 -- An inline shell for Python 2 developers.
 Py2Lab51 is an inline IDE for productive development in Python 2:
 -provides an interactive IPython shell.
 -downloads and installs a package from the PyPI.org repo.
 -builds an EXEcutable (binary) file.
 -makes a (.C) and a (.SO) extension, also builds an EXEcutable (binary) file.
 -provides a <sample.pyx> that helps with vectorization.
 
 
